      "content": "# Dependencies\n\n## Internal Dependencies\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    App[\"app.py\"]\n    Routes[\"Blueprint routes\"]\n    Services[\"services\"]\n    Config[\"config.py\"]\n    Templates[\"templates\"]\n    Workflows[\"workflow json\"]\n    Db[\"SQLite db\"]\n\n    App --> Routes\n    App --> Services\n    Routes --> Services\n    Routes --> Config\n    Routes --> Templates\n    Services --> Config\n    Services --> Db\n    Services --> Workflows\n```\n\n### Text Alternative\n- The launcher depends on route modules and service modules.\n- Route modules depend on services, configuration, and templates.\n- Services depend on SQLite and workflow JSON files.\n\n### `app.py` depends on `app` and `app.services.db`\n- **Type**: Runtime\n- **Reason**: Bootstraps the application and initializes persistence.\n\n### Route blueprints depend on `app.services.*`\n- **Type**: Runtime\n- **Reason**: Delegate HTTP orchestration to shared helper modules.\n\n### `media_store.py` depends on `db.py`\n- **Type**: Runtime\n- **Reason**: All SQL operations share the same connection lifecycle.\n\n### `comfyui.py` depends on workflow JSON files\n- **Type**: Runtime\n- **Reason**: Workflows are patched dynamically before submission.\n\n## External Dependencies\n\n### Flask\n- **Version**: Unpinned\n- **Purpose**: HTTP framework and template rendering\n- **License**: BSD-3-Clause\n\n### Werkzeug\n- **Version**: Unpinned\n- **Purpose**: Request/response utilities and filename sanitization\n- **License**: BSD-3-Clause\n\n### Requests\n- **Version**: Unpinned\n- **Purpose**: ComfyUI and Ollama HTTP calls\n- **License**: Apache-2.0\n\n### Psutil\n- **Version**: Unpinned\n- **Purpose**: Auxiliary stats tooling support\n- **License**: BSD-3-Clause\n\n### OpenCV Python Headless\n- **Version**: Unpinned\n- **Purpose**: Generate thumbnails for external movie files\n- **License**: Apache-2.0\n\n## Runtime External Systems\n- ComfyUI on LAN HTTP endpoint\n- Ollama on LAN HTTP endpoint\n- Mounted filesystem shares containing media outputs\n"
